<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Guatemala-Rebels     03-15 0105</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Guatemala-Rebels,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>Four Soldiers Killed, Two Wounded in Guerrilla Ambush</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GUATEMALA CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Leftist rebels ambushed an army patrol in
the northwest highlands, killing four soldiers and wounding two, the
army said.
   Rebels set off a Claymore mine Sunday as the patrol was traveling
near the village of Cuarto Pueblo 90 miles northwest of Guatemala
City, the army said in a communique. The dead included a second
lieutenant, it said.
   The Guerrilla Army of the Poor, one of three rebel groups
fighting for about 27 years to overthrow military or
military-dominated governments, operates in the area, carrying out
sporadic attacks and propaganda missions.
</TEXT>
