<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--LockedIn     03-15 0170</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Locked In,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Teen-Ager Spends Night Locked In School Restroom</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WAUCHULA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Saturday night was the loneliest night of
the week for 17-year-old Stacy Powell, and a frantic one for her
mother.
   Stacy stopped by Hardee Senior High in the community 50 miles
southeast of Tampa on Saturday afternoon to use the telephone, and
ended up getting locked in the bathroom after a teacher locked the
restroom without checking to see if it was empty.
   When she did not return home by midnight, her family notified the
Hardee County Sheriff's Office, which issued a missing person
bulletin.
   Meanwhile, Stacy's screams for help went unheard and she settled
in for the night on the cold tile floor of the bathroom. She was
rescued Sunday morning, when a volunteer putting up missing person
posters about her disapperance heard Stacy's screams for help.
   Stacy said she was excited because she knew her parents were
worried about her.
   ``It was the worst thing I've ever been through,'' said her
mother, Bonnie.
</TEXT>
