<HEAD>Gannett Announces Publishers Of Chambersburg and Elmira Papers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nancy Monaghan, managing editor of USA Today,
was appointed president and publisher of the Chambersburg (Pa.)
Public Opinion, according to a statement by Gannett Co. Inc., owner
of the newspapers.
   Ms. Monaghan, who has been on the USA Today staff since the paper
was started in 1982, succeeds Pat Frantz, who becomes president and
publisher of the Elmira (N.Y.) Star-Gazette, also a Gannett
newspaper.
   Ms. Frantz, 45, had served as advertising director at Elmira in
1986 and later that year became publisher of the newspaper in
Chambersburg, the company statement said.
   Ms. Monaghan, 43, was national editor of USA Today before
becoming managing editor for news at the paper in 1984. She joined
Gannett in 1977 at the Rochester (N.Y.) Democrat and Chronicle.
