<HEAD>Three Set Fire To Station During Robbery Attempt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three men set fire to a subway token booth in a
robbery attempt early today, injuring the clerk, police said.
   Transit police spokesman Al O'Leary said men passed a note
demanding money to the clerk in the booth. When she pushed the note
back out through the window, they poured a flammable liquid around
the booth and lit a match, he said.
