<HEAD>Fighter Jet Crashes at MacDill</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two crew members of an F-16 ejected safely as
their fighter jet crashed Wednesday at MacDill Air Force Base, an
Air Force spokeswoman said.
   The pilot and student pilot were hospitalized for observation and
reported in good condition.
   Spokeswoman Airman Tina Freeman said the plane was on a training
mission when it crashed on base shortly before noon.
   The Air Force said it had not immediately determined the extent
of damage to the sophisticated, multimillion-dollar plane. A board
of officers was appointed to investigate the crash.
   MacDill, home base to many F-16s, is on the tip of a peninsula
jutting into Tampa Bay southeast of downtown Tampa.
