<SECOND>AM-Mexico-Bus Crash,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bus-Truck Crash Kills 27</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TLAXCALA, Mexico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus trying to pass another on a curve
slammed into a tractor-trailer, and the other bus crashed into a
ravine, killing 27 people and injuring 25 others Wednesday,
officials said.
   Federal Highway Police said the drivers of the bus and truck that
crashed into each other on the two-lane road were among the dead,
the government news agency Nomitex reported. It quoted police as
saying the other bus driver fled the scene.
   Juan Manuel Elias Carmona, a highway police commander, said the
crash occurred in Santa Ana Chiautempan, about four miles south of
Tlaxcala, capital of Tlaxcala state. Tlaxcala is 60 miles east of
Mexico City.
