<HEAD>London Shares Weaker In Calm Midday Trading</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: will be led after closing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices weakened in calm midday trading
Wednesday.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was down 13.9
points at 2,114.5 around 12:15 p.m local time, although off its
midmorning worst level of 2,109.0.
   The index started at its maximum 2,124.6 and continued its
decline throughout the morning.
   Volume totaled 332.2 million shares, compared with 373.9 million
the same time Tuesday.
   Shares prices were buoyed Tuesday by Chancellor of the Exchequer
Nigel Lawson's fiscally tight budget. But on Wednesday, a perception
that the budget contained nothing specifically advantageous for the
equity market depressed prices a bit.
