<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-May     03-15 0239</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-May,0250</SECOND>
<HEAD>May Reports Profit For Quarter, Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   May Department Stores Co. reported Wednesday
that its earnings were sharply higher in the fourth quarter and for
the fiscal year.
   During the three months ended Jan. 28, the company netted $298
million, or $2.10 a share, on sales of $4 billion. That was 30
percent higher than earnings of $230 million, or $1.52 a share, and
sales of $3.2 billion, in the previous year.
   Included in the latest quarter was a pre-tax charge of $35
million, the company said.
   For the fiscal year, May earned $503 million, or $3.42 per share,
14 percent higher than the previous year's net income of $440
million, or $2.88 a share. Sales rose to $11.5 billion from 9.7
billion.
   ``The year was an excellent one for May,'' said Chairman David C.
Farrell. ``Each of our retail segments contributed to these record
results, making this our 14th consecutive year of both record
earnings and sales and enabling the company to surpass the $500
million milestone in net earnings.''
   Farrell said May was ``well positioned for 1989 and beyond,
including a very aggressive expansion program.''
   He said the company will add 11 new department stores, four
discount stores and 140 Payless ShoeSource stores this year. He said
May would also remodel 25 department stores, expanding 11 of them.
   May is one of the largest retailers in the nation, operating
3,091 stores.
</TEXT>
