   Hospital Corp. of America rose [ to 49\ in active trading after
the company's shareholders approved a buyout by a management group.
   Sea Containers Ltd. gained 1] to 45~ on top of an 8{-point jump
Tuesday, when investors learned that Stena AB of Sweden has acquired
an 8.17 percent interest in the company and may seek to gain control
of it.
   Mesa Limited Partnership dropped ~ to 11}. The partnership
disclosed plans to reduce its quarterly payout later this year
because of weak natural-gas prices.
   Smithkline Beckman rose 1\ to 54 after signing an agreement with
a British firm for the development and marketing of a new treatment
for arthritis.
   As measured by Wilshire Associates' index of more than 5,000
actively traded stocks, the market increased $12.37 billion, or 0.42
percent, in value.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks gained
.74 to 166.67.
   Standard &amp; Poor's industrial index rose 2.02 to 342.97, and S&amp;P's
500-stock composite index was up 1.53 at 296.67.
   The NASDAQ composite index for the over-the-counter market
advanced .97 to 406.98. At the American Stock Exchange, the market
value index closed at 331.79, up 1.26.
